Description: 
        My Little Ticket :ticket:
        =========================
        
        
        .. image:: https://travis-ci.org/iksaif/my-little-ticket.svg?branch=master
           :target: https://travis-ci.org/iksaif/my-little-ticket
           :alt: Build Status
        
        
        .. image:: https://coveralls.io/repos/github/iksaif/my-little-ticket/badge.svg
           :target: https://coveralls.io/github/iksaif/my-little-ticket?branch=master
           :alt: Coverage Status
        
        
        UI and API to show an aggregate status of your services.
        
        
        .. image:: doc/my-little-ticket.png
           :target: doc/my-little-ticket.png
           :alt: My-Little-Ticket screenshot
        
        
        *This is currently under active development and not ready for production.*
        
        Quickstart
        ----------
        
        .. code-block:: bash
        
           virtualenv venv -p python3
           source venv/bin/activate
           cp examples/local_settings.py defcon/
           pip install -e .
           pip install -r requirements.txt
           ./manage.py migrate
           ./manage.py migrate --run-syncdb
           ./manage.py createsuperuser
           ./manage.py runserver
        
        Configuration
        -------------
        
        See `local_settings <examples/local_settings.py>`_.
        
        Authentication
        --------------
        
        This project is using `django-allauth <https://django-allauth.readthedocs.io/en/latest/>`_.
        
        API
        ---
        
        Simply go to ``/swagger/`` or ``/api/`` to see what can be done.
        
        Plugins
        -------
        
        Strategies
        ^^^^^^^^^^
        
        A strategy is a way to score and organize tickets on a board. Check
        `base.py <my_little_ticket/plugins/base.py>`_ and `default.py <my_little_ticket/plugins/default.py>`_ for an example.
        You'll need to implement only a few functions.
        
        And add it to your settings.py:
        
        .. code-block:: python
        
           MLT_STRATEGIES = [
              ...
               'my_module.MyStrategy',
           ]
        
        Plugins
        ^^^^^^^
        
        A plugin is a way to fetch ticket from a source. Currently this project
        can only fetch tickets from JIRA, but you can easilly create your own plugin,
        take a look at `base.py <my_little_ticket/plugins/base.py>`_ and
        `jira <my_little_ticket/plugins/jira.py>`_ to know more.
        
        .. code-block:: python
        
           MLT_PLUGINS = [
               ...
               'my_module.MyPlugin'
           ]
        
